{
  "files": [
    {
      "repo": "grafana/grafana",
      "path": "pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/client.go"
    },
    {
      "repo": "grafana/grafana",
      "path": "pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/config.go"
    },
    {
      "repo": "grafana/grafana",
      "path": "pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/fake.go"
    },
    {
      "repo": "grafana/grafana",
      "path": "pkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/client.go"
    },
    {
      "repo": "grafana/grafana",
      "path": "pkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/config.go"
    }
  ],
  "text": "HTTP Client Retry and Timeout Configuration:\n\npkg/components/loki/lokihttp/config.go defines the Config struct with BackoffConfig and Timeout fields. BackoffConfig is of type backoff.Config (from github.com/grafana/dskit/backoff), and Timeout is a time.Duration for the HTTP client.\n\npkg/components/loki/lokihttp/client.go implements the HTTP client with retry logic using backoff. The sendBatch() method creates a backoff.New(c.ctx, c.cfg.BackoffConfig) instance and uses backoff.Wait() and backoff.Ongoing() to control retries when sending batches. It retries on 429 (Too Many Requests) and 5xx status codes. The client.Timeout is set from config (line 175), and individual requests use context.WithTimeout(ctx, c.cfg.Timeout) for timeout enforcement (line 331). The StopNow() method (line 376) stops the client without waiting for retries by calling c.cancel().\n\npkg/components/loki/lokihttp/fake.go provides a fake/stub Client implementation for testing purposes. It implements the StopNow() method as an empty implementation (line 39).\n\ngRPC Client Retry and Timeout Configuration:\n\npkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/config.go defines the Config struct with Retries (uint) and Timeout (time.Duration) fields for the gRPC client configuration.\n\npkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/client.go implements the gRPC client with retry configuration using grpcretry middleware. The grpcRetryOption() method (lines 82-88) sets up gRPC retry interceptor using grpcretry.UnaryClientInterceptor with grpcretry.WithMax(c.cfg.Retries) to limit the maximum number of retries. The timeoutCtx() method (lines 90-96) creates a context with timeout using context.WithTimeout() if cfg.Timeout > 0, or context.WithCancel() if timeout is not set. This timeout context is used for the Write() operation when pushing requests to Loki."
}

